# Gradle Conventions

## Kotlin DSL
- Prefer `build.gradle.kts` (Kotlin DSL) for new projects
- Type-safe accessors for plugins and extensions
- Explicit task configuration with `tasks.named<>` or `tasks.withType<>`

## Version Catalogs
- Centralize dependencies in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`
- Reference in build files: `libs.spring.boot.starter.web`
- Version bundles for related dependencies

## Dependency Management
- `implementation` for production deps, `testImplementation` for test deps
- Use `platform()` for BOM imports
- `dependencyLocking` for reproducible builds
- Check for unused dependencies with `gradle-dependency-analysis-plugin`

## Gradle Wrapper
- Always use Gradle Wrapper (`gradlew` / `gradlew.bat`)
- Commit `gradle/wrapper/` to version control
- Keep wrapper version pinned and updated

## Task Avoidance
- Use `tasks.register` instead of `tasks.create` for lazy configuration
- Configure tasks only when they will execute

## Testing
- Surefire equivalent: `tasks.test { useJUnitPlatform() }`
- Integration tests: separate source set with `testing-jvm` plugin
- JaCoCo: `jacoco` plugin with `jacocoTestReport` task

## Build Commands
- `./gradlew build` -- full build with tests
- `./gradlew check` -- run all checks
- `./gradlew dependencies` -- dependency tree audit
